text: Chambray is a commune in the Eure department of northern France, 13 km northeast of Évreux on the north bank of the Eure River. The Château de Chambray, in the north of the commune, is the ancestral home of the Marquis de Venevelles d'Espagne. ==Population== ==See also== *Communes of the Eure department ==References== *INSEE Category:Communes of Eure
